    <p class="section-tag">Guide</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">AI Search ROI – The Business Case</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/five-signal-model.svg" alt="The Five Signal Model for AI search" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI search visibility is infrastructure, not a campaign. Unlike paid advertising, it does not stop when the budget stops. The position built in month two is the foundation for month six.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">The Measurement Gap</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">When an AI system recommends your business, the user often gets what they need – your name, what you do, a reason to consider you – without clicking through to your site. Your analytics record nothing. Your brand was surfaced, your expertise referenced, someone made a decision based on what the AI said about you. And your dashboard shows zero.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Brand search volume and direct traffic are better proxies than session data for measuring AI search impact.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">The Compounding Effect</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI visibility compounds. Each month of consistent signals makes the position more stable. The businesses that build this now, while most competitors are not thinking about it, will be extremely difficult to displace once AI systems have established confidence in them.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">We engineer deliberately what established brands accumulated passively. The mechanism is the same. The timeline is different.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Timeline</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Months 1-2:</span> AI crawlers have access. Priority pages restructured. Ecosystem live.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Months 2-4:</span> Content across key clusters. Extended ecosystem. All six platforms showing coverage.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Months 4-8:</span> Full site and content to standard. Full ecosystem active.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">8+ months:</span> Self-reinforcing. Very difficult for competitors to displace quickly.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>

